{
  "stem": "1061.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That means that you were not 'privileged'-- quote, unquote-- 'privileged' to work outside of the camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was nothing to do in the camp, so they had a pile of rocks on one end and a pile of rocks on the other end.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had one group of women carrying rocks from here to that pile, and then the other group from here to there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You see?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This was to wear you out, to beat you down, to exhaust you so that they wouldn't even have to burn you anymore because you will do it two yourself, so to say.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Did you work besides-- after that?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, this is only the first phase.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The quarantine was about a month.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we arrived, I'd say, at the end of July, early August-- so probably all of August, we were in so-called quarantine.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then by September, we were sent to cut marshes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were some escapees by then from Auschwitz-- not that we knew it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I know now why we were assigned to cut the marshes.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The reason was that apparently the Germans did not want marsh land around the camp for-- because these people who were running-- might want to run away-- would hide there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we-- we were sent onto this job to cut marshes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We stood in water.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was incredible.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The food-- the-- the food that was given out in-- first of all, you know, in Auschwitz, you had to be out, counted-- you-- roll call, every morning.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If they didn't like-- if somebody was missing, you could stand there for two hours.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If they didn't like the way you lined up, you were beaten.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
